node.title: Woman charged with starting six fires on South Australia's Yorke Peninsula
node.alt: A fire burns in a paddock
node.description: A 48-year old Minlaton woman is charged with six counts of starting a bushfire after the Country Fire Service responded to the blazes near Maitland yesterday.
node.content: ["A woman has been charged with deliberately lighting\u00a0six grass fires on the Yorke Peninsula yesterday afternoon.", "Emergency services were called to a grass fire in Agery \u2014 north of Maitland \u2014 about 3pm.", "Another five fires were then found within an hour, between Agery and Urania \u2014 south of Maitland \u2014 a distance of about 40 kilometres.\u00a0", "All were quickly contained by the Country Fire Service\u00a0and there were no reports of property damage in the dryland farming area.\u00a0", "The 48-year-old Minlaton woman has been charged with six counts of starting a bushfire.", "She will appear in the Port Pirie Magistrates Court on Monday.\u00a0", "The bushfire danger season began on the Yorke Peninsula last Monday.", "Yesterday's weather on the Yorke Peninsula was windy with temperatures in the mid 20s.", "A bushfire in the lower Yorke Peninsula in November 2019 damaged 11 properties.\u00a0"]
